{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"96b8d838-b989-43ce-9c34-8a9be41fe5fe","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Update both base images:\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0\n```\n\n**Then verify:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version        # confirm 11.0.100 SDK is installed\ndotnet build            # check for breaking API changes\ndotnet test             # run your tests\n```\n\nAlso review the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update any NuGet packages (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"65c326d3-b378-4ff0-a5e4-683b7c76412a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":343,"requestId":"6C35:F41F2:E4CBFA:10C91AF:69FE9363"},"id":"060d6de8-c8e2-438f-ad6f-9801f6821384","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:52:47.527Z","parentId":"df38da43-78b3-4299-9419-a56e00907f84"}
